content: Finally reached out to an old mentor for advice on quantum computing. They pointed me to some resources. This rabbit hole is deep.
Started to compile a list of key figures in AI and blockchain. Planning to reach out for potential mentorship or collaboration. Networking feels like the next big step.
Had a minor setback with the AI integration. The model isn't adapting as expected. Back to the drawing board for some tweaks.
Just finished a 5-day mindfulness retreat. It was intense but enlightening. Learning to let go of stress and focus on the present is a game changer.
Attended a conference on cognitive augmentation. Met some brilliant minds. Exchanged ideas about how AI can enhance human cognition. Mind blown.
Began writing a paper on the implications of quantum-resistant blockchains in financial markets. This might open doors to academic circles.
The AI project is coming along. We're now testing real-time data integration. The accuracy is improving, but there are still kinks to work out.
Had an insightful conversation with a colleague about the ethical implications of AI in trading. It's not just about efficiency; it's about responsibility.
Just got an email from a blockchain expert I reached out to. They're interested in discussing my paper. Looks like my networking efforts are paying off.
The mindfulness practice is paying dividends. Handled a high-stress situation at work with much more composure than I would have a month ago. Progress.
